         <abstract>
            <p>A stability theory is developed for general difference approximations to mixed initial boundary value problems. The results are applied to certain commonly used difference approximations which are stable for the Cauchy problem, and different ways of defining boundary conditions are analyzed.</p>
          </abstract>
